---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Nick Battaglia"
  description="JD/MBA candidate at Indiana University Maurer School of Law and Kelley School of Business, building at the intersection of legal practice and machine learning."
>

  <section class="container pt-20 pb-16 max-w-2xl">
    <p class="pill mb-5">About</p>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-light text-text mb-8 leading-tight">
      Law, software,<br/>and what's between them.
    </h1>

    <div class="prose-custom space-y-5 text-text-dim leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I'm a JD/MBA candidate at Indiana University — Maurer School of Law
        and Kelley School of Business, graduating in 2029. Before law school
        I worked in data science and product quality / product management,
        most recently at Acrelec, where I built a GDPR-compliant LightGBM
        pricing model that improved average revenue per order by 2% and led
        a company-wide audit of the BI offering. That background means I
        tend to think about legal problems as systems with inputs, outputs,
        failure modes, and optimization targets.
      </p>
      <p>
        My current focus is legal AI — specifically how retrieval-augmented
        generation can make M&amp;A diligence faster and more consistent.
        Argus is the portfolio project exploring that: a full Corrective
        RAG pipeline backed by Vertex Gemini 2.5 Flash, Cohere Embed v4
        and Rerank 3.5, Neon pgvector, and Supermemory, with a Drafting
        &amp; Review Hub for generating and reviewing contracts against
        an M&amp;A playbook grounded in the CUAD and MAUD academic datasets.
      </p>
      <p>
        At Maurer I serve as President of the Data, AI &amp; Tech Association,
        an Associate on the IP Theory journal, a Stewart Fellow, and an
        Elmore Scholar. This summer I'll be a legal intern with OPL
        GunnerCooke in Budapest, working primarily on data privacy,
        regulatory, and legal-technology matters. Outside of that I'm
        interested in transaction structuring, corporate governance, and
        the intersection of securities law with emerging technology.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="card">
        <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Education</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text font-medium">Indiana University</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-dim">Maurer School of Law — JD</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-dim">Kelley School of Business — MBA</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-dim mt-2">University of Iowa — BBA, Business Analytics &amp; Information Systems</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-2">Expected 2029 (JD/MBA) · 2024 (BBA)</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Focus areas</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-2">
          {['Legal AI', 'M&A', 'Corporate law', 'RAG systems', 'Data privacy', 'Contract automation'].map(area => (
            <span class="pill">{area}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mt-5 mb-2">Credentials</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          <span class="pill">Series 65</span>
          <span class="pill">AZ-900</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
